    "body": "### Problem\n\n`vim.fs.rm()` does not normalize the path first. Because of this, `vim.fs.rm('~/Documents/removeme')` does not work. This is not clearly documented.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. `touch ~/Documents/removeme`\n2. `nvim --clean`\n3. `:lua vim.fs.rm('~/Documents/removeme')`\n4. ENOENT error\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nFile ~/Documents/removeme is removed. If that behaviour is undesirable (for whatever reason), this should at least be documented similar to `vim.fs.dirname()` and `vim.fs.parents()`:\n\n> (...) (not expanded/resolved, the caller must do that).\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nd93e150888558ddab1722a81427c5943c5be87df\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nn.a.\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nMacOS 14.8\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nGhostty 1.3.0-main+1003a7e62\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-ghostty\n\n### Installation\n\nfrom source",
