            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "I'd warn about introducing tilde expansion by default. While it is great quality of life for fixed paths, when you start using variables things can break. Since `~` is a valid name for a path, if a relative path inside a variable happens to start with `~`, unexpected things could occur. Especially for `vim.fs.rm()` where removing a folder named `~` could end up removing a user's $HOME if it was expanded. It's not hard to write `vim.fs.rm(vim.fs.abspath(...))` for situations where expansion is wanted.",
