            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> `~` expansion is a terrific quality-of-life addition, all the `vim.fs` functions should do the same thing as far as expansion goes\n\nSeems unwise to expand things everywhere, because:\n\n- sending things \"literally\" becomes much more awkward\n- there is a performance cost.\n\nBut maybe special-casing `~/` everywhere is fine. No objection from me...\n\nMeanwhile, updated the docs: https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/37096\n\nSome functions like `fs.dir()` do expand, but most others don't :(\n\n> Alternatively or in addition, an `expand = true` option could be added to `{opts}`.\n\nI think we should avoid adding redundant mechanisms. Caller can opt-in via `normalize()` already. If that's too awkward for some reason then let's find out why :)",
