            "body": "> how is `'./' .. path` (or `vim.fs.joinpath('.', path)`) to enforce current dir only much more awkward?\n\nThere are other things that are expanded, such as env vars.\n\n> Also the common case where you actually need both, `vim.fs.abspath(vim.fs.normalize(path))`\n\nWhen? normalize() should be a superset of abspath(). I didn't want to add abspath() but there were some edge cases that required it, would need to review the PR discussion for details.\n\n\n\n",
